{"title":"SimLauncher: Launching Sample-Efficient Real-world Robotic Reinforcement Learning via Simulation Pre-training","domain":"ROBOTICS","seeds":[{"problem":"Real-world robotic reinforcement learning is sample-inefficient due to difficult exploration and heavy reliance on costly human demonstrations.","method":"SimLauncher pre-trains a visuomotor policy in a digital-twin simulator and uses its rollouts to accelerate real-world RL. It bootstraps the critic in a hybrid off-policy RL setup (RLPD) with demonstrations from both simulated rollouts and limited real-world rollouts of the pre-trained policy, sampling 25% D_sim, 25% D_real, and 50% online replay per batch. During interaction, it proposes actions by comparing the BC (pre-trained) action and the RL policy action via a Boltzmann distribution over Q-values (p ∝ exp(βQ)), and uses the selected action for bootstrap targets. This combination substantially improves sample efficiency and achieves near-perfect success across multi-stage and dexterous tasks compared to IBRL/RLPD baselines."},{"problem":"Transferring visuomotor policies from simulation to the real world is hindered by visual/physical sim-to-real gaps, and critics can overfit if trained only on simulation data.","method":"The framework builds task-specific digital twins and trains policies via a privileged-to-visual distillation pipeline: learn a state-based (privileged) policy with RL in sim, generate successful trajectories, then behavior clone a visuomotor policy using RGB + proprio. It mitigates sim-to-real gaps by calibrating physics/cameras, randomizing camera pose in sim demos, applying visual augmentations during BC, and masking backgrounds at train/test time with SAM2-tracked segmentations. A small number of real rollouts from the pre-trained policy are added to the demo buffer and sampled equally with simulated demos to regularize the critic and prevent value underestimation on real transitions."},{"problem":"Success-only simulated demonstrations may provide limited state coverage, weakening bootstrapping for real-world RL.","method":"SimLauncher augments demonstration coverage by constructing hybrid demos: it uniformly collects rollouts throughout state-based policy training and post-renders image observations, yielding broader coverage of intermediate and failure states. Experiments show simulated demos alone can effectively bootstrap real-world RL, and that increasing simulated demo scale or using hybrid demos further improves sample efficiency."}]}
